{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Hold a binding referendum on the future of the TV licence.",
        "additional_details": "The government should give the general public a binding referendum on the future of the TV Licence before the next royal charter,the questions should be how the BBC is funded:\r\n\r\n1) remain the same, the licence will remain as it is now \r\n2) change to a Subscription service and be able to have advertising, the bbc will get its funds from subscribers and by showing adverts this will also decriminalise the licence as there will be no need for enforcement.",
        "background": "The TV Licence has been a cause of much concern to the general public over a long period of time with many petitions and debates taking place. The BBC say they are answerable  to the general public yet the public get very little say into there funding, its now time to let the public have there say.",
